Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a graph-processing system specifically for the GPU, which is a parallel computing architecture. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses various graph primitives and their performance on different GPU architectures. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possibility as the paper evaluates the performance of various optimization strategies. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possibility as the paper focuses on programming the GPU, which is a hardware architecture. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper discusses a high-level programming model for developing graph primitives on the GPU.
